content:
Configure your settings for WhatsApp, Facebook Messenger, Apple Messages for Business, or SMS Messaging channels.

To set up and edit Messaging channels: Configure Messaging
To view channels: View Setup and Configuration

From Setup, enter Messaging in the Quick Find box and select Messaging Settings.
Find your channel in the list, and click Edit in its action menu.
IMPORTANT In enhanced Messaging channels and Messaging for In-App and Web, clicking Edit shows only some of the channel settings.

Update your settings and save your changes.

Channel Name
Name of this channel.
API Name API name of this channel.
Business Hours (Available only if Einstein Bots are in use) The operating hours for your business, when agents are available.
Messaging Platform Key 
(Not editable)
SMS: Phone number associated with this channel.
WhatsApp: Phone number associated with this channel.
Facebook Messenger: Facebook page ID associated with this channel.
Apple Messages for Business: Apple Messages identifier.

Active (Not editable) Indicates whether the channel is available for customers to send messages to.
Routing
Enable Advanced Routing 
(Visible in standard channels) Select this option to route this channel’s messaging sessions based on the logic in the specified Omni-Channel flow.
Flow Definition (Visible in standard channels if Enable Advanced Routing is selected) The Omni-Channel flow used to route messages in this channel.
Fallback Queue (Visible in standard channels if Enable Advanced Routing is selected) The queue that receives messaging sessions that the Omni-Channel flow is unable to route.
Routing Type
The type of routing for this channel.

Queue 
The queue that messages sent to this channel are routed to. You can’t delete queues.
Routing Configuration (Visible in standard channels if Routing Type is set to Channel Skills) The routing configuration used to route messages in this channel.
Skill (Visible in standard channels if Routing Type is set to Channel Skills) The skill or skills associated with this channel.
